&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Technical Assent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Technical Assent is a federal consulting firm that helps government organizations improve services, programs, and mission outcomes through human-centered design, customer experience, research, analytics, and practical implementation support. We work with federal clients to understand customer and employee needs, measure experience, generate actionable insights, and help leaders make evidence-based decisions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Technical Assent is seeking an Associate Consultant or Consultant to support customer experience, employee experience, and applied research projects for federal clients. This role is ideal for an emerging survey and research professional who can help design, configure, test, field, analyze, and report on survey-based research programs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be hands-on, detail-oriented, comfortable working with data, and able to support multiple workstreams under the direction of senior researchers, project managers, and client leads. This person will help turn research plans and survey instruments into well-executed data collection efforts, clean reporting outputs, and useful insights for clients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a consulting role, so the candidate should be comfortable working directly with federal clients, managing deadlines, contributing to high-quality deliverables, and adapting to the needs of different projects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Associate Consultant / Consultant will support federal CX, EX, and applied research projects by performing responsibilities such as:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting survey design, question development, survey logic, respondent flow, and instrument refinement under the direction of senior team members.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Configuring, testing, and maintaining surveys in Qualtrics and other&amp;nbsp; survey or voice-of-customer platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Building and testing survey logic, skip patterns, display logic, embedded data, contact lists, email distributions, reminders, and data exports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conducting survey quality assurance to verify accuracy, usability, accessibility considerations, data capture, and respondent experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitoring survey fielding, response activity, distribution issues, and data quality during active data collection periods.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cleaning, organizing, and preparing survey data for analysis and reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting development of quantitative analysis, descriptive statistics, response summaries, cross-tabulations, trend analysis, and open-ended response review.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Developing tables, charts, dashboards, and reporting products using Excel, Qualtrics dashboards, Power BI, Tableau, or similar tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Helping translate data into clear findings, implications, and recommendations for federal clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting client meetings, status updates, project documentation, and deliverable development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinating with project managers, researchers, designers, analysts, and client stakeholders to keep work on schedule and aligned with project goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintaining documentation for survey instruments, data files, codebooks, dashboards, reporting assumptions, and quality control steps.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contributing to a collaborative consulting environment focused on quality, responsiveness, and practical client value.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
