&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Technical Assent supports the Office of the Deputy Assistant Secretary of War for Logistics (ODASW(Log)) under a high-visibility enterprise logistics contract spanning policy development, program governance, and strategic advisory services. This role is a manager for the contractor team embedded within the Commercial Support to Operations (CSO) Directorate — the DoW office responsible for enduring policy and program management across Operational Contract Support (OCS), Vendor Threat Mitigation (VTM), and Private Security Contractors (PSC). The CSO lead will be a key point of contact for the Directorate, overseeing a team of subject matter experts working at the intersection of DoW-wide logistics policy, senior governance, and operational program execution.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The CSO Lead serves as a senior contractor advisor and manager for Technical Assent&#39;s support to the CSO Directorate, directing day-to-day task execution across a demanding, multi-workstream environment. This role requires an ability to make sound, timely judgments about competing priorities and workload allocation across a portfolio of policy, governance, and program management activities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team Leadership and Client Engagement&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and direct contractor team members supporting the CSO Directorate, planning task timelines, allocating staff resources, and ensuring quality and on-time delivery of all contract deliverables.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and sustain a trusted advisor relationship with the CSO Director and government leads, seeing individual workstreams in the context of Directorate-level mission priorities and broader ODASW(Log) strategic objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advise the Director on integrating portfolio requirements and lines of effort across all CSO activities; develop and deliver communications products that convey new concepts and policy areas to diverse senior DoW stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work at client site (Alexandria, VA) 5 days per week, with flexibility for occasional remote work (situational telework).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Policy and Program Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apply extensive expertise across DoW logistics and commercial support operations to provide technical insight and recommendations on the development, maintenance, and management of CSO Directives, Instructions, Regulations, and Manuals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Analysis, Reporting, and Governance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze strategic guidance, policies, doctrine, and standard operating procedures; develop well-reasoned recommendations and POAMs to improve CSO business process effectiveness and efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee production of CSO reports, reviews, policy drafts, concept briefings, and assessments; develop integrated analysis that supports government decision-making and senior leader engagement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support governance of the CSO portfolio through preparation and execution of working groups, boards, and cross-functional coordination events, including the B2C2WG; provide POAM and execution planning, facility coordination, and on-site support for events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Managing Consultant Level Expectations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Managing Consultant at Technical Assent, this individual is expected to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor team members in developing and applying knowledge, skills, and abilities within core capability areas and professional practice.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pursue continuous learning and professional growth within core capability areas and areas of domain expertise.&lt;/li&gt;
